dismissalText.commentary: Corey Collymore lbw b Chopra 3 (31b 0x4 0x6) SR: 9.67

commentTextItems.html: gets on his backfoot, rapped straight in front of the stumps, up goes the fingers

commentPostTextItems.html: 5 wickets for Chopra, a victory for India and the cup to the Indians
India win by 88 runs
And the DMC Cup by a margin of 2-1
Presentations
Losing captain Lara
Credit must be given to the Indian bowlers
Powell played a tremendous innings
Some of our shots were not warranted
Powell has only played a handful of one-day matches
It is nice to see youngsters coming up and playing with enthusiasm
We played bad today but we have a new tournament starting on Thursday
Man of the match award coming up...
Rahul Dravid - for his batting and 4 catches
Dravid: I had a difficult time last year, but I have worked hard this year
Man of the cup now...
To Ganguly! a crazy choice
Sunil Gavaskar is the adjudicator. Justifies his selection by his batting in the first match, bowling in the second and captaincy in the third...
Ganguly now coming up to get the winning cheque
Ganguly picks up the DMC Cup
The whole Indian team with the cup for a photo session
That is all folks, be here tomorrow as the Australia A team faces the Indian A team
While the day after, Pakistan and West Indies play in Toronto
Good bye

commentPostTextItems.html: A slip and a forward short leg

commentTextItems.html: on the legs, off the pads to backward short leg. A happy Kambli fields

stories.title: India defeat West Indies to win series
stories.summary:
Toronto, Sept 15: Rahul Dravid cracked 77 and held four brilliant
catches as India defeated West Indies by 88 runs to win the
Toronto Cricket Festival series of the three One-day
Internationals 2-1 here on Tuesday

stories.title: Windies crushed
stories.summary:
Another spell-binding demonstration of clean, uncomplicated power
hitting by Ricardo Powell saved the West Indies from complete
humiliation but not from heavy defeat by India in the final of
the DMC Cup here yesterday
